  "instructions": [
    "Heat 2 tablespoons of low-fat vegetable oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and saut\u00116\u00042e until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and grated ginger and cook for an additional 1-2 minutes, until fragrant.",
    "Add the crushed black cardamom pods, ground cumin, ground coriander, turmeric powder, and cayenne pepper. Cook for 1 minute, until the spices are fragrant.",
    "Add the low-sodium vegetable broth and bring to a simmer.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and add the chickpeas and sour cream. Simmer, uncovered, for 10-15 minutes, or until the liquid has thickened slightly.",
    "Season with salt to taste.",
    "Serve the Kik Alicha over low-fat injera or rice."
